    <item>
      <title>Selection Tool in Maya</title>
      <link>https://jaechoidev.github.io/notes/selection-tool/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 27 Mar 2022 21:08:07 -0700</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://jaechoidev.github.io/notes/selection-tool/</guid>
      <description>I&amp;rsquo;ve been working on the selection tool which can select objects by an proxy object. The proxy can be a cube or sphere, and same logic is implemented to the camera distance selection as well. The main concept came from a blog post about frustum culling. It refers something like basic collision logic. To do this, I needed normal vector and a point for each planes. Every objects in the scene will be checked if the farthest bbox point is on the same direction of plane normal or not.</description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Hi, my name is Jae.</title>
      <link>https://jaechoidev.github.io/about/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 13 Feb 2022 20:25:04 -0800</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://jaechoidev.github.io/about/</guid>
      <description>Hi, my name is Jae. I’m working as a Lighting TD at ICON Creative Studio, Vancouver, Canada. I have worked on 3D Animation industry for about 4 years. My career was started as lighter and compositor and then kept moving to the technical side step by step. I like learning and digging something new.
My interests are shading, rendering and cutting-edge real time related technology. For better understanding on them, I’m taking CS courses as part time student.</description>
